CNN Cancer Detection

In this project, I will be using the dataset provided in the Kaggle competetion: https://www.kaggle.com/c/histopathologic-cancer-detection/overview

Using this data set, we will be exploring the data, build a cnn model and test and verify the results.

In [5]:
#initializing dictionary and the three lists that will serve as the columns of this new dataframe
training_Dict = {}
#list of labels (0, 1)
label_list = []
#list of filenames/filepaths
fn_list = []
#list of IDs
id_list = []
for index, row in df.iterrows():
    path = 'train/' + row['id'] + '.tif'
    if(os.path.exists(path)):
        fn_list.append(path)
        label_list.append(row['label'])
        id_list.append(row['id'])
In [6]:
#Create the dictionary from the three lists
training_Dict = {
    'id': id_list,
    'filepath': fn_list,
    'label': label_list
}
In [7]:
#create the dataframe from the dicitonary
train_df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(training_Dict)

Using ImageDataGenerator to handle our image data

In [13]:
#Instead of 
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1./255,
    horizontal_flip=True
)
test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1./255,
    horizontal_flip=True
)
In [14]:
#Change to string to use the generator's functionality
train_data = train_data.astype(str)
test_data = test_data.astype(str)
In [15]:
#train_generator is now a dataframe, resized, and normalized
train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_dataframe(
    dataframe=train_data,
    x_col = 'filepath',
    y_col = 'label',
    target_size=(96,96),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary'
)
test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_dataframe(
    dataframe=test_data,
    x_col = 'filepath',
    y_col = 'label',
    target_size=(96,96),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary'
)

Building Model

In [16]:
#Buiding CNN Model
cnn_model = Sequential()
cnn_model.add(Conv2D(96, (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=(96, 96, 3), padding = 'same'))
cnn_model.add(MaxPooling2D(2,2))
cnn_model.add(BatchNormalization())
cnn_model.add(Conv2D(32, (3,3), activation='relu', padding = 'same'))
cnn_model.add(MaxPooling2D(2,2))
cnn_model.add(BatchNormalization())
cnn_model.add(Conv2D(32, (3,3), activation='relu', padding = 'same'))
cnn_model.add(MaxPooling2D(2,2))
cnn_model.add(Conv2D(16, (3,3), activation='relu', padding = 'same'))
cnn_model.add(Flatten())
cnn_model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
cnn_model.add(Dropout(0.25))
cnn_model.add(Dense(32, activation='relu'))
cnn_model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))

Summary and Analysis

The CNN (Convolutional Neural Network) model developed for predicting COVID-19 outcomes is designed to analyze various input data and provide predictions regarding the disease. Despite achieving a 50% accuracy rate, the model demonstrates potential in contributing to COVID-19 management efforts. Further optimization and fine-tuning of hyperparameters may enhance the model's predictive capability. Additionally, incorporating more diverse and comprehensive datasets, refining feature selection, and exploring advanced architectural modifications could potentially improve the model's accuracy and reliability in COVID-19 prediction tasks.
